<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Former Cop Guilty of 54 Sex Charges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FAYETTEVILLE, W.Va. (AP) -- A former Gauley Bridge police chief  
accused of sexual assault against three boys has been convicted on 
54 counts, 
</P>
<P>
	Lee Edward Jones, 38, collapsed after the verdicts were read  
Friday. He later was taken to the Southern Regional Jail in 
Beckley, pending sentencing next week. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones, who was arrested about a year ago, had testified during  
the trial that the allegations were a conspiracy against him by 
State Police and prosecutors. At one point, dozens of people in the 
Fayette County town of 700 rallied in his support. 
</P>
<P>
	But prosecutor Kristen Keller said it was the strength of  
testimony from three witnesses, males ages 14 to 27, who detailed 
acts that occurred from 1983 until either 1995 or 1996. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones faces a separate eight-count indictment involving a fourth  
boy, but Keller wasn't sure after the verdict if those charges will 
be pursued. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones also faces charges in South Carolina involving an alleged  
assault of a juvenile at a Myrtle Beach motel room in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
