<CATEGORY> international </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Volcano Near Mexico City Spouts Ash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MEXICO CITY (AP) -- The Popocatepetl volcano near Mexico City has  
again spouted plumes of ash and water vapor, civil defense 
authorities reported. 
</P>
<P>
	The activity on Friday followed an explosion late Thursday that  
sent ash falling on the city of Puebla, 65 miles east of Mexico 
City, the National Center for Disaster Prevention reported. 
</P>
<P>
	More light ash showers were likely to fall from Friday's  
explosions, the center said. 
</P>
<P>
	The 18,000-foot volcano is located just 50 miles southeast of  
Mexico City. The biggest of Friday's exhalations lasted about 11 
minutes, authorities said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
