<HEADLINE> Kenyon Wins Women's Swimming Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OXFORD, Ohio (AP) -- Erica Carroll set a second meet record  
Saturday in winning her third individual title to lead Kenyon to 
its 16th consecutive NCAA Division III women's swimming and diving 
championship. 
</P>
<P>
	Carroll, named the meet's outstanding swimmer, also was a member  
of a winning relay team for the third time. 
</P>
<P>
	Kenyon amassed 664.5 points to easily outdistance Denison (503),  
Williams (355.5), California-San Diego (348) and Hope (218). 
</P>
<P>
	Carroll won the 200-yard backstroke in a meet record 2 minutes,  
1.78 seconds. On Friday, she set the 100-yard butterfly meet record 
and also won the 100-yard backstroke. 
</P>
</TEXT>
