<HEADLINE> Furlough Wins at Aqueduct </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Trainer Shug McGaughey saddled his third winner  
of Aqueduct's Distaff Breeders' Cup Handicap in 11 years Saturday 
when Furlough outgamed heavily-favored Catinca for a head victory 
in the 45th running of the $174,350, Grade II event. Tomorrows 
Sunshine was another length back. 
</P>
<P>
	McGaughey sent out Cadillacing to win the Distaff for owner  
Ogden Phipps in 1988 and repeated with Recognizable in 1995. 
</P>
<P>
	Furlough went seven furlongs in 1:23.1 on the fast track to  
score her first stakes win since taking Saratoga's Grade III 
Honorable Miss Stakes last Aug. 5. The 5-year-old Easy Goer mare 
earned $104,510 with her seventh win in 25 career starts. 
</P>
<P>
	Furlough returned $30.20, $7.20 and $4.60. Catinca paid $2.60  
and $2.30 and Tomorrows Sunshine was $3.70 to show. 
</P>
</TEXT>
