<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fuel Tanker Explodes, Killing Two </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FULLERTON, Calif. (AP) -- A tanker carrying 8,000 gallons of fuel  
overturned and exploded on a freeway, hurling fiery debris and 
killing a motorist and the trucker. 
</P>
<P>
	The 44-year-old driver of the tanker succumbed to his burns  
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	``I just saw this guy come out of truck fully engulfed in flames  
and just running,'' witness Vanessa Juarez said of the Friday 
accident. ``His whole body was on fire.'' 
</P>
<P>
	People used their jackets to beat out the flames.  
</P>
<P>
	The motorist, burned beyond recognition, was found in the  
wreckage of a car more than an hour after the crash, authorities 
said. The car and tanker collided, but it was unclear whether that 
happened before or after the truck went out of control. 
</P>
<P>
	The force of the explosion hurled flaming pieces of the truck  
more than 60 yards. 
</P>
<P>
	Fullerton is about 30 miles southeast of downtown Los Angeles.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
