<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Affleck: I Wasn't Always a Hunk </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Ben Affleck, unattached again after romancing  
Gwyneth Paltrow, wasn't always the sought-after bachelor that movie 
stardom has made him. 
</P>
<P>
	``As a kid, I was the kind of guy who got dumped a lot,'' he  
says in the April issue of Cosmopolitan magazine, remembering 
himself as a gangly, clumsy teen. ``I don't think the ladies were 
saying, `I'm looking for somebody awkward and beanpole-like who 
doesn't have control of his own limbs.''' 
</P>
<P>
	With film credits including ``School Ties,'' ``Good Will  
Hunting'' and ``Armageddon,'' the 26-year-old actor has improved 
his dating quotient considerably since high school. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm definitely amused at seeing my love life on the evening  
news,'' he admits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
